    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-21T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/378: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of State (<persName corresp="#p_SHL1"
                            type="from">Stimson</persName>) to the Minister in Liberia (<persName
                            corresp="#p_MCE1" type="to">Mitchell</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-21T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 21, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. The Department is in receipt of a letter from <persName corresp="#p_LCGT1"
                        >Colonel Lewis</persName> informing it that he has “tendered to the
                    President of Liberia his resignation as military adviser of the Liberian
                    Frontier Force”, effective July 15, 1932.</p>
                <p>You may inform <persName corresp="#p_MCL1">McCaskey</persName> informally. As you
                    are aware, in view of our not having recognized the present administration, we
                    would not be in a position to designate a successor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
